six children were killed and four other family 
members injured thursday when a fire broke out in their home 
officials said 
fourteen people all members of the same family lived in the 
narrow onestory home that was heavily damaged by the fire shortly 
before 6 am said fire capt john welch some were able to escape 
by jumping out windows but the children 13 and under were trapped 
flames were spewing from the windows just like an inferno 
said neighbor myrtle bell the kids inside were screaming they 
just couldnt get no help 
the fire apparently started in a kerosene space heater in the 
basement of the home welch said 
the father woke up and saw one of the sons adjusting or doing 
something with the heater and then there was a flash welch said 
lt joe marcinkiewicz said investigators were trying to determine 
whether the heater was defective or if it was being filled with the 
wrong type of fuel 
possibly he was adding gasoline rather than kerosene 
marcinkiewicz said that happens all too much 
marcinkiewicz identified the victims as tony harris 13 antonio 
hurn 8 jerrly brooks 4 terrly harris 2 rodney b davis 1 and 
tierra hurn 1 
four people were taken to barnes hospital 
joe hurn 42 was listed in serious condition with burns over 10 
percent of his body said hospital spokesman john miller 
hurns wife rosalie 40 their daughterinlaw katrina harris 
22 and cochee hurn 14 also were listed in serious condition 
suffering from smoke inhalation miller said 
the heater had been placed in front of the basements outside 
door prohibiting exit welch said windows and doors at the back of 
the house had metal bars on them 
