when mary beth blakeman sent her 
dearest high school friend a christmas card in 1958 she didnt 
expect to get the card back the next year 
but she did and 30 years later blakeman 45 of okauchee and 
lenora mulock 46 of menomonee falls are still sending the 
timeworn greeting card when the holiday season rolls around 
thats usually the first thing i look for in the mail mulock 
said 
blakeman said the two were sophomores at menomonee falls high 
school in 1958 
thats when mulock read a newspaper story about two men staying 
in contact by reusing the same card each year and she decided to 
give it a try 
we were inseparable in high school this helped us keep in 
touch wed get the card each year call each other and laugh well 
probably keep sending it until one of us dies 
the card shows a young girl handing a hot water bottle to a 
snowman 
on the inside are the signatures of blakeman who first sent the 
card and mulock who sent it back a year later 
on the back are 28 more years of signatures including the 
additional names of husbands and children as they arrived 
this year blakeman sent the card minus the names of two children 
who no longer live at home 
now well start taking away the names because the kids are 
moving out mulock said 
next christmas blakeman is expecting the card to arrive at her 
door for the 16th time 
if we lost it id feel terrible mulock said especially 
after all these years 
