<TEXT>
a federal judge ruled today that portions of a 
1952 law allowing deportation of aliens for advocating world 
communism are unconstitutional because they violate immigrants 
first amendment rights 
us district judge stephen v wilson also threw out a 
congressional exception to a subsequent law which gave free speech 
rights to all immigrants except members of the palestine liberation 
organization 
congress he said already has passed sufficient laws dealing 
with terrorism and his decision didnt diminish the governments 
power to deport aliens for reasons unrelated to their speech 
we do not minimize the governments concerns with foreign 
policy or national security interests wilson said reading his 
decision in a crowded courtroom nor do we in this day and age 
deny the real and lethal threat that terrorism poses for our 
nation 
our decision today however will not significantly deplete the 
governments arsenal in combatting terrorism he said 
by invoking the mccarranwalter provisions he said the 
government is trying to stifle certain ideas from entering our 
society from certain aliens 
our society however was built on the premise that only 
through the free flow of ideas can our nation grow and prosper he 
added 
wilson addressed both the 36yearold mccarranwalter act and a 
1987 statute the foreign relations authorization act the latter 
act gave aliens the same first amendment rights as citizens when it 
came to deportation proceedings but made several exceptions such as 
the denial of first amendment rights to members of the plo 
the four provisions of the mccarranwalter act which he ruled 
unconstitutional provide that aliens may be deported if they 
advocate or are affiliated with a group that advocates the doctrines 
of world communism totalitarian dictatorship or the unlawful 
destruction of property 
the plo exception that was struck down provided for deportation 
of plo members who advocated the same ideologies 
the judge ruled in the case of eight immigrants who appealed 
deportation proceedings begun under the mccarranwalter act after 
they were arrested by federal agents and held without bail 
