mrs harris who is serving a 15yearstolife sentence at the 
bedford hills correctional facility became eligible for clemency in 
august when she served half her minimum sentence the unofficial 
benchmark 
clemency commutes a sentence and allows an inmate to become 
eligible for parole final release from prison must be granted by 
the state parole board 
inmates generally have to serve their minimum term before 
appearing before the parole board in mrs harris case that would 
mean 1996 
she declined a request for an interview and has not commented on 
the issue she wrote a letter applying for clemency but it has not 
been released 
health can be a factor in clemency approval mrs harris suffered 
at least one heart attack in prison her age and good prison record 
also may be grounds she has been active in the childrens center at 
the prison has taught and wrote two books 
cuomos decisions on clemency are based on advice from a 
threeperson executive clemency board which reviews opinions from 
those involved in a case the clemency process is kept under close 
wraps until a decision is announced 
each case is decided on its own merits said cuomo spokesman 
terry lynam theres no concern of public relations if an inmate 
is deserving of clemency he or she will get it 
mrs harris applied for clemency in 1986 but it was denied on 
the ground that she had not served half her minimum sentence 
