soviet studios have recently gained greater independence but 
remain dependent on government financing of production and 
distribution said vladimir padunov a professor at wheaton college 
in norton mass and an authority on the soviet film industry 
chernyck said one difficulty in writing the screenplay was a 
different in approaches to humor our jokes and humor are not so 
fast as american humor when jeremy told us a joke we would start 
laughing after five minutes he said 
the film will be in both english and russian with no dubbing or 
subtitles but characters will usually speak no more than a sentence 
or two so that viewers can figure out the meaning much of the 
humor will be visual leven said 
in one scene leven said the american and a soviet counterpart 
become covered in mud and are ushered into a tiny bathroom to 
undress the two are left standing naked facetoface 
the soviet igor looks at peter and shrugs to show he is 
unimpressed then says america 
peter looks back and shrugs to show he too is unimpressed and 
says russia 
