<TEXT>
as investigators centered on sabotage as the 
cause of a pan am jumbo jet disaster aviation experts said thursday 
a crash could be caused by a relatively small bomb if the blast 
damages a planes sensitive control systems 
depending on where a bomb is placed even a relatively small 
explosive device can fatally cripple an aircraft were not talking 
about the kinds of explosive force you would need to cripple a 
tank said john mazor a spokesman for the private air line pilots 
association 
kenneth plunkett a representative of the aviation safety 
institute agreed noting that its not the size of the bomb its 
where it is placed 
both mazor and plunkett stressed that they had no firsthand 
details about what caused the crash of pan am flight 103 in scotland 
wednesday all 258 people aboard the boeing 747 jetliner were 
killed along with 22 people on the ground in the village of 
lockerbie 
