<TEXT>
corpses were strewn on a golf course 
and children played beside twisted airplane wreckage thursday in 
this village scarred physically and emotionally by the pan am crash 
residents recalled whooshing noises and tremendous flames as the 
stricken boeing 747 jumbo jet roared low overhead spewing pieces 
over the rolling countryside and finally crashing in fragments 
across their streets and houses wednesday evening 
all 258 people aboard pan am flight 103 from frankfurt to new 
york via london died and as many as 22 people were killed on the 
ground some in cars hit by wreckage officials said the number of 
people on the plane was lowered when it was found that an airline 
employee was counted twice 
it is beyond ones comprehension murmured prime minister 
margaret thatcher who toured the village it is beyond ones 
imagination you have to come here to see it and to realize 
a long deep crater tore a black scar along a row of houses 
other homes drenched in flaming aviation fuel were gutted 
survivors comforted each other felt lucky to be alive and tried 
to clean up some of the mess in the town of 2500 people 
in a yard next to the main street lay the cover of one engine 
but the fence and adjacent building were undamaged children 
bicycled around a chunk of fuselage and the grocer boarded up his 
shattered store front 
scorched pillows lifejackets and fragments of clothing lay 
scattered in gardens chunks of metal some as small as coins and 
others two feet in diameter had sliced through roofs and shattered 
windows in homes and cars 
charred dollar bills a mudspattered seatbelt and tattered 
copies of the pan am inflight magazine added to the melancholy scene 
lockerbies town hall became a makeshift morgue as firefighters 
recovered remains strewn about town eight bodies lay on a 
neighboring golf course covered in tarpaulins and guarded by police 
four miles outside town the nose cone of the blueandwhite 
jumbo jet was tipped on its side in a muddy field 
therell be no christmas this year as far as lockerbie is 
concerned said bobby scott a builder who had just finished work 
wednesday night when he heard the explosion 
he dashed out to see the jet heading toward the gas station and 
watched the disaster unfold yards from him 
the plane was breaking up as he saw it come over a hill about 200 
