here is a thumbnail sketch of samuel skinner 
who was named thursday by presidentelect bush as his cabinet 
secretary for the department of transportation 
 
skinner is 50 years old married and the father of two 
he received an undergraduate degree in accounting from the 
university of illinois in 1960 and a law degree from depaul 
university in 1966 
he is currently a senior partner in chicago office of the sidley 
amp austin law firm 
since 1984 skinner has served as chairman of the regional 
transportation authority of northeastern illinois 
skinner also served as an assistant us attorney in chicago from 
19681975 and was appointed us attorney in chicago by gerald ford 
in 1975 when thenus attorney james thompson was elected governor 
of illinois 
