purchase of cluett stock when in fact he primarily used money 
that he had raised from a small group of wealthy businessmen he 
made a 7 million profit by later selling the stock 
the indictment further alleged bilzerian illegally hid ownership 
of 58000 shares of hh robertson by selling it to the los 
angelesbased brokerage jefferies amp co with the understanding that 
he would buy it back later 
this activity commonly known as stock parking can be used 
to avoid securities and exchange commission reporting requirements 
and acquire stock positions in companies without disclosing them 
publicly 
