minutes shortly after a chaotic opening in which the market was 
swamped with sell orders linked to reports that some dockworkers had 
returned to their jobs in the brazilian port of santos the busiest 
coffee port in the worlds largest coffeeproducing country 
the strike which began dec 13 has been a key factor in 
coffees dramatic price surge from less than 125 a pound on dec 1 
to the twoyear high of 159 a pound recorded wednesday 
other fundamental factors underpinning coffees gains include 
tight us warehouse stocks delayed shipments from central america 
a rainslowed harvest in colombia and a drought in the prime growing 
areas of brazil 
these bullish developments have been playing out against a 
backdrop of rising demand coffee consumption peaks each year during 
the winter months in the northern hemisphere 
