presidentelect bush named louis sullivan to be 
secretary of health and human services thursday pushing aside a 
controversy over sullivans abortion views he also announced three 
other cabinet choices and an environmental chief as he neared 
completion of his administrations top ranks 
the selection of sullivan the first black in bushs cabinet had 
been opposed by antiabortion groups especially after an interview 
last weekend in which he said women should have a right to choose 
abortion he has taken a strongly antiabortion stance in comments 
since then 
bush characterized sullivan as a man with great credentials 
and said the 55yearold medical educator shared most of his own 
