shareholders of nl industries inc overwhelmingly 
have approved a previouslyannounced restructuring that spins off 
the companys petroleum services business into a new publiclyheld 
company officials said thursday 
the restructuring effective thursday leaves nl with only its 
chemical operation 
under the plan the company redeemed its series c preferred stock 
and declared a onefor10 reverse split of its outstanding common 
stock preferred shareholders could get either one share of 
postsplit stock or 1566 cash for each of their series c shares 
the transactions leave preferred shareholders controlling 90 
percent of the surviving company and former common shareholders 
holding 10 percent 
nl common stockholders also received on a prorata basis all of 
the outstanding common stock of the newly spunoff petroleum 
business baroid corp 
valhi corp nl industries parent will control about 52 percent 
of baroids 61 million outstanding common shares valhi will control 
about 66 percent of nls 66 million outstanding common shares 
baroid corp common stock and postsplit nl common stock were 
expected to begin trading friday on the new york and pacific stock 
exchanges under the symbols brc and nl respectively 
houstonbased baroid is a worldwide supplier of petroleum 
services nl as restructured will consist primarily of the 
business of nl chemicals inc 
